Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \n‘The same fabric of space we inhabit, where we imagine these elaborate dreams, and haven’t even ever seen a fraction of what we really are…Truth be told we nuclear souls, Indigo, in the cold, new to these zones…Carbon based body make a suitable home, my temporary temple, I’m soon to be gone.’ ~ excerpt from ‘Makeshift Kingdom’ by Sweatshop Union

Name: Invoking the Sacred Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \n'We return thanks to our mother, the earth, \nwhich sustains us. \nWe return thanks to the rivers and streams, \nwhich supply us with water. \nWe return thanks to all herbs, \nwhich furnish medicines for the cure of our diseases. \nWe return thanks to the moon and stars, \nwhich have given to us their light when the sun was gone. \nWe return thanks to the sun, \nthat has looked upon the earth with a beneficent eye. \nLastly, we return thanks to the Great Spirit, \nin Whom is embodied all goodness, \nand Who directs all things for the good of Her children.' \n~ Iroquois prayer

White Tara Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \nTārā is a meditation deity worshiped by practitioners of the Tibetan branch of Vajrayana Buddhism to develop certain inner qualities and to understand outer, inner and secret teachings such as karuṇā (compassion), mettā (loving-kindness), and shunyata (emptiness). Tārā may more properly be understood as different aspects of the same quality, as bodhisattvas are often considered metaphors for Buddhist virtues. Her seven eyes are symbolic of watchfulness and compassion.
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 16x24" Stretched Canvas, 20x30" Stertched Canvas, Choose An Option

Name: Athene Artemisia Print
Short description: \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nSIZE \n— 11″ x 17″ in \n \nNOTE \n— Dispatched within 3 business days \n— Shipped with backing board and plastic sleeve \n \nAthene or Athena is a Greek goddess of wisdom, courage, inspiration and the arts. She is often said to have had "bright eyes", which is thought to be the reason why she shares the same root word with the owl. Athene is often depicted with an owl, seeing through the dark and bringing wisdom and guidance to those who ask. Artemis is the goddess of the wild lands, reminding us of our origins and our instincts.
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 30x22" Stretched Canvas, 40x30" Stretched Canvas, Choose An Option

Wolf is the sage, who after many winters upon the sacred path and seeking the ways of wisdom, returns to share new knowledge with the tribe. Wolf is both the radical and the traditional in the same breath. When the Wolf walks by you - you will remember.' - Robert Ghost Wolf

Name: Abydos Canvas
Short description: CANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— All of our products are dispatched within 3 business days \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \nFor the Ancient Egyptians, Abydos was one of the holiest sites in the world. As the cult centre of the god Osiris and gateway to the underworld (believed to lie under the nearby hills), it was a popular place of pilgrimage and burial. This image is a tribute to the ancient magic and rich culture of Egypt.
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 24x10" Stretched Canvas, 32x14" Stretched Canvas, Choose An Option

Name: Pinecone Buddha Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled The Golden Elixir. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for delivery \n \n'We are shaped by our thoughts; we become what we think. When the mind is pure, joy follows like a shadow that never leaves.' ~ Buddha \n \n  \n \n

Name: Sky Diamonds Tapestry
Short description:
This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Sky Diamonds \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display as wall decor \n \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for delivery \n \n'By observing natural scientific discoveries through a perception deepened by meditation, we can develop a new awareness of reality. This awareness could become the bedrock of a spirituality that is not based on the dogmas of a given religion, but on insights into a higher and deeper meaning. I am referring to the ability to recognize, to read, and to understand the firsthand revelations.' ~ Albert Hofmann \n

Name: Galactic Wolf Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Crystalline Wolf Totem. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for delivery \n \n'Wolf is the Grand Teacher. Wolf is the sage, who after many winters upon the sacred path and seeking the ways of wisdom, returns to share new knowledge with the tribe. Wolf is both the radical and the traditional in the same breath. When the Wolf walks by you – you will remember.’ ~ Robert Ghost Wolf

Name: Wisdom Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Wisdom \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \nThe Owl is said to represent psychic energy, independence, wisdom, the third eye, spirituality, protection, intuition, supernatural power, connection with night time and the moon, mystery, magic, secrets, intelligence, transition, telepathy, the afterlife and magic.

Name: White Tara Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled White Tara. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \n‘White Tara’ represents compassion, longevity and serenity. Her seven eyes are symbolic of watchfulness and compassion.

Name: Luminous Return Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled The Luminous Return. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \n'When I let go of what I am, I become what I might be.' ~ Lao Tzu

Name: Athene Artemisia Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Athene Artemisia. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \nAthene is often depicted with an owl, seeing through the dark and bringing wisdom and guidance to those who ask. Artemis is the goddess of the wild lands, reminding us of our origins and our instincts.

Name: Crystalline Dreams Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Crystalline Dreams. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \n‘The same fabric of space we inhabit, where we imagine these elaborate dreams, and haven’t even ever seen a fraction of what we really are…Truth be told we nuclear souls, Indigo, in the cold, new to these zones…Carbon based body make a suitable home, my temporary temple, I’m soon to be gone.' ~ excerpt from ‘Makeshift Kingdom’ by Sweatshop Union

Name: Secret of the Emerald Forest Print
Short description: \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nSIZE \n— 11″ x 17″ in \n \nNOTE \n— Dispatched within 3 business days \n— Shipped with backing board and plastic sleeve \n— This is a triptych piece which accompanies The Secret of the Golden Forest and Secret of Samsara \n \n'A human being is a part of the whole called by us universe, a part limited in time and space. One experiences one's self, one's thoughts and feeling as something separated from the rest, a kind of optical delusion of his consciousness. This delusion is a kind of prison for us, restricting us to our personal desires and to affection for a few persons nearest to us. Our task must be to free ourselves from this prison by widening our circle of compassion to embrace all living creatures and the whole of nature in its beauty.' ~ Albert Einstein

Depictions of skulls in ancient eastern iconography serve diverse forms and functions. In Tibetan Buddhism skulls represent the universal quality of emptiness; phenomena we experience is the result of our attaching meaning to experience and lacks any inherent nature in itself. They remind us of the natural, circular progression of life and death.

Name: Celestial Tiger Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— All of our products are dispatched within 3 business days \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \nIn Chinese folk tales, tigers kill evil men and protect good men. Tiger charms are used to keep away disease and evil, and babies are given colourfully embroidered tiger shoes for protection. Tiger images frequently decorate children's clothing and tops. The "Tiger Claw" (Hu Chao) amulet is believed to ward off sudden fright and give the wearer the courage of the tiger. Because the tiger wards off disasters, it is popular as one of the nine gods worshipped at the New Year Festival. Tiger images are painted on the walls of homes and temples to keep away evil spirits. Dragon-Tiger Mountain is the name for the palace of the hereditary head of the Daoist religion, located in the Dragon Tiger Mountains of Jiangxi Province, east of the capital city of Nanchang. Zhang Daoling (Chang Tao-ling), the "First Master of Heaven" in the Daoist religion, is depicted riding a tiger and carrying a demon-dispelling sword as he escorts the dead to their final destination. A Daoist legend tells of two brothers who took on the role of protecting human beings by capturing demons and throwing them to tigers.

type="4_4" _builder_version="3.25" custom_padding="|||" custom_padding__hover="|||"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" _builder_version="3.27.4" background_size="initial" background_position="top_left" background_repeat="repeat"]

Since I was young I’ve always felt that the way our society interprets masculine and feminine qualities is totally backwards. The celebrated qualities of the alpha male; being aggressive and quick to anger, dominant and overbearing, insatiably lustful and sexually compulsive… I see these as motivated by weakness and fragility, by a lack of self-awareness and enslavement to a frail ego.

\n

In my world, a ‘real man’ is a man that can cry without shame, a man that bear the pain of facing his own ego, a man that can truly see his flaws and insecurities, a man that is sensitive to how he makes others feel, a man that come overcome the temptations of violent implosion reactions when triggered, a man that can share true intimacy without objectifying or manipulating others, a man that venerates women. The qualities we see as feminine; sensitivity, empathy, nurturance and sweetness… I see these as being powerful and courageous; to be sensitive, to really feel and care in this hurting world necessities tremendous courage and bravery. Its heartbreaking how many of our sisters, daughters and mothers have been abused and face structural oppression every day, but its encouraging that the collective consciousness is growing increasingly intolerant of sexual abuse and toxic masculinity. The resilience and strength of women the world over is a source of constant inspiration. This is dedicated to the fierce cosmic force of the female spirit. RESPECT.

\n

‘A strong woman in her essence is a gift to the world’

\n

- Native American saying

\n

 सर्वमङ्गलमाङ्गल्ये शिवे सर्वार्थसाधिके । शरण्ये त्र्यम्बके गौरि नारायणि नमोऽस्तु ते ॥

\n

ॐ जयंती मंगल काली भद्रकाली कपालिनी । दुर्गा क्षमा शिवा धात्री स्वाहा स्वधा नमोऽस्तु‍ते ॥

[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]

Name: Space Sutra Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nNOTE \n— All of our products are dispatched within 3 business days \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \n'Although the corpus of teachings attributed to the Buddha, if taken as a whole, embodies many contradictions, these contradictions are only apparent. Teachings are appropriate to the context in which they are given and thus their contradictions evaporate. The Buddha’s teachings are to be used like ladders, or, to apply an age-old Buddhist image, like a raft employed to cross a river. There is no point in carrying the raft once the journey has been completed and its function fulfilled. When used, such a teaching transcends itself.' ~ Paul Williams

Name: Astral Wolves Tapestry

Name: Dryad Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Dryad. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \n'Just as the ancients danced to call upon the spirits in nature, we too can dance to find the spirits within ourselves that have been long buried and forgotten.' ~ Anna Halpri

Name: Dark Raven Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Dark Raven. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \n'Open here I flung the shutter, when, with many a flirt and flutter, \nIn there stepped a stately raven of the saintly days of yore; \nNot the least obeisance made he; not a minute stopped or stayed he; \nBut, with mien of lord or lady, perched above my chamber door — \nPerched upon a bust of Pallas just above my chamber door — \nPerched, and sat, and nothing more.'  ~ Edgar  Allan Poe

Name: Sacred Projection Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \n'You might think of the ethnosphere as the sum total of all thoughts and dreams, myths, ideas, inspirations, intuitions brought into being by the human imagination since the dawn of consciousness. The ethnosphere is humanity’s great legacy. It’s a symbol of all that we are, and all that we can be as an astonishingly inquisitive species.' ~ Wade Davis
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 20x30" Stretched Canvas, 30x45" Stretched Canvas, Choose An Option

Name: Erawan Print
Short description: \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nSIZE \n— 11″ x 17″ in \n \nNOTE \n— Dispatched within 3 business days \n— Shipped with backing board and plastic sleeve \n \nThe elephant, in its majesty, conjures notions of strength, wisdom and courage, and has been considered symbolic of these traits across diverse cultures.

Name: Lynx Guide Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \nLynx is the keeper of lost magic and occult knowledge. Lynx is the guardian of secrets and, more importantly, the knower of the secrets.
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 30x20" Stretched Canvas, Choose An Option

Name: Crystalline Thoughts Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \n. . . c r y s t a l l i n e   t h o u g h t s . . \n \n 'You are like a candle. Imagine you are sending light out all around you. All your words, thoughts and actions are going in many directions. If you say something kind, your kind words go in many directions, and you yourself go with them. We are …transforming and continuing in a different form at every moment.' ~ Thich Nhat Hanh \n \n
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 20x26" Stretched Canvas, Choose An Option

Name: Shishi Canvas
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \nIn China, the lion is the master of all felines, the defender of law, and the protector of sacred buildings. It is a symbol of power, success, and strength. In Japan, the Shishi (獅子) is a noble beast who protects the entrances of temples, shrines and tombs.
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 16x26" Stretched Canvas, Choose An Option

Name: Secret of The Forest Canvas - 42x8" Stretched Canvas
Alchemical Memories
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas printed with water-based inks to yield the maximum colour saturation and longevity available \n \nPAPER PRINTS \n— Giclee printed on archival glossy paper \n \nNOTE \n— Please Allow 2-3 Weeks for Printing and Delivery \n \n'By observing natural scientific discoveries through a perception deepened by meditation, we can develop a new awareness of reality. This awareness could become the bedrock of a spirituality that is not based on the dogmas of a given religion, but on insights into a higher and deeper meaning. I am referring to the ability to recognize, to read, and to understand the firsthand revelations.' ~ Albert Hofmann
Attribute 1 value(s): 11x17" Paper Print, 16x24" Stretched Canvas, 20x30" Stretched Canvas

\n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nNOTE \n— Please Allow 2-3 Weeks for Printing and Delivery \n

Kami (神) are the spirits or phenomena of nature that are worshipped in Shinto, the traditional religion of Japan.  They can be elements of the landscape, forces of nature, animals, ancestral spirits and embodiments of virtuous qualities. In Shinto, Kami are not separate from nature but are of nature. They are manifestations of Musubi (結び), the interconnecting energy of the universe. Kami are believed to be hidden from this world, and inhabit a complementary existence that mirrors our own; shinkai (神界, "the world of the kami”). To be in harmony with the awe-inspiring aspects of nature is to be conscious of kannagara no michi (随神の道 or 惟神の道, "the way of the kami").

\nThis image is a companion piece to Spectral Crossing. Both images depict an imagined dream sequence of a glimpse into the hidden world.

Name: Space Sutra Tapestry
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Space Sutra. \n \nFEATURES \n— Made with high-quality, durable and soft poly-tech fabric \n— High-definition, full colour artwork \n— Hanging loops for easy display \n \nSIZE \n— 60" x 90" in / 152 x 228 cm \n \nNOTES \n— Care Instructions: Machine Washable, Dryer Safe \n— These tapestries are made to order \n— Please allow 2-3 weeks for printing before shipment \n \n‘Although the corpus of teachings attributed to the Buddha, if taken as a whole, embodies many contradictions, these contradictions are only apparent. Teachings are appropriate to the context in which they are given and thus their contradictions evaporate. The Buddha’s teachings are to be used like ladders, or, to apply an age-old Buddhist image, like a raft employed to cross a river. There is no point in carrying the raft once the journey has been completed and its function fulfilled. When used, such a teaching transcends itself.’ ~ Paul Williams

Name: Mythical Guardian Pin (Copy)
Short description: FEATURES \n— Double Posted Enamel Pin \n— Limited Edition of 200 \n \nSIZE \n— Approx. 2.5" in x 2.5″ in \n \nBarong is a lion-like creature and character in the mythology of Bali, Indonesia. He is the king of the spirits, leader of the hosts of good, and enemy of Rangda, the demon queen and mother of all spirit guarders in the mythological traditions of Bali. The battle between Barong and Rangda is featured in Barong dance to represent the eternal battle between good and evil.

Name: Raven's Call Holographic Sticker
Short description: This design is based on Mugwort’s original artwork titled Dark Raven. \n \nFEATURES \n— Thick, durable die-cut vinyl \n— Resistant to scratches, water and sunlight \n— Holographic vinyl has a vibrant rainbow effect that changes with light and perspective \n \n \nSIZE \n— Approx. 3″ in x 3″ in \n \nThe Inuit say that Raven was born out of the darkness. He was weak and lost. As he began traveling aimlessly experiencing the world, he realized that he was the Raven Father, Creator of All Life. Once he realized who he was, he gathered up his strength and flew out of the darkness to a new place which he called earth, but he was still alone, so he decided to create plants. As he flew around exploring this new world, he came upon a man whom the legend claims was the first of the Inuit people. Raven fed the man and taught the man to respect the world around him. Soon after, a woman came to be and Raven taught the both of them how to cloth themselves, build shelter, and make canoes to travel the water. As the two bred and spawned children, Raven cared for their children and educated them as he had done before.

Short description: \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nSIZE \n— 11" x 17" in \n \nNOTE \n— Dispatched within 3 business days \n— Shipped with backing board and plastic sleeve \n \nIn Chinese folk tales, tigers kill evil men and protect good men. Tiger charms are used to keep away disease and evil, and babies are given colourfully embroidered tiger shoes for protection. Tiger images frequently decorate children's clothing and tops. The "Tiger Claw" (Hu Chao) amulet is believed to ward off sudden fright and give the wearer the courage of the tiger. Because the tiger wards off disasters, it is popular as one of the nine gods worshipped at the New Year Festival. Tiger images are painted on the walls of homes and temples to keep away evil spirits. Dragon-Tiger Mountain is the name for the palace of the hereditary head of the Daoist religion, located in the Dragon Tiger Mountains of Jiangxi Province, east of the capital city of Nanchang. Zhang Daoling (Chang Tao-ling), the "First Master of Heaven" in the Daoist religion, is depicted riding a tiger and carrying a demon-dispelling sword as he escorts the dead to their final destination. A Daoist legend tells of two brothers who took on the role of protecting human beings by capturing demons and throwing them to tigers.

\n

Kami(神) are the spirits or phenomena of nature that are worshipped in Shinto, the traditional religion of Japan.  They can be elements of the landscape, forces of nature, animals, ancestral spirits and embodiments of virtuous qualities. In Shinto, Kami are not separate from nature, but are of nature. They are manifestations of Musubi (結び), the interconnecting energy of the universe. Kami are believed to be hidden from this world, and inhabit a complementary existence that mirrors our own; shinkai (神界, "the world of the kami”). To be in harmony with the awe-inspiring aspects of nature is to be conscious of kannagara no michi (随神の道 or 惟神の道, "the way of the kami").

\n

This image is a companion piece to Ethereal Vision. Both images depict an imagined dream sequence of a glimpse into the hidden world.

Name: Space Sutra Print
Short description: \n \nCANVAS \n— Printed on archival ph-neutral canvas using water-based inks to yield maximum colour saturation and longevity \n— Stretched on 3/4 inch″ stretcher bars \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nNOTE \n— All of our products are dispatched within 3 business days \n— Please allow 2 - 3 weeks for printing and shipping \n \n'Although the corpus of teachings attributed to the Buddha, if taken as a whole, embodies many contradictions, these contradictions are only apparent. Teachings are appropriate to the context in which they are given and thus their contradictions evaporate. The Buddha’s teachings are to be used like ladders, or, to apply an age-old Buddhist image, like a raft employed to cross a river. There is no point in carrying the raft once the journey has been completed and its function fulfilled. When used, such a teaching transcends itself.' ~ Paul Williams

Name: Dark Raven Print
Short description: \n \nPAPER / GICLEE PRINTS \n— Printed on archival glossy paper \n \nSIZE \n— 11″ x 17″ in \n \nNOTE \n— Dispatched within 3 business days \n— Shipped with backing board and plastic sleeve \n \n  \n \nThe Inuit say that Raven was born out of the darkness. He was weak and lost. As he began traveling aimlessly experiencing the world, he realized that he was the Raven Father, Creator of All Life. Once he realized who he was, he gathered up his strength and flew out of the darkness to a new place which he called earth, but he was still alone, so he decided to create plants. As he flew around exploring this new world, he came upon a man whom the legend claims was the first of the Inuit people. Raven fed the man and taught the man to respect the world around him. Soon after, a woman came to be and Raven taught the both of them how to cloth themselves, build shelter, and make canoes to travel the water. As the two bred and spawned children, Raven cared for their children and educated them as he had done before.

Kami (神) are the spirits or phenomena of nature that are worshipped in Shinto, the traditional religion of Japan.  They can be elements of the landscape, forces of nature, animals, ancestral spirits and embodiments of virtuous qualities. In Shinto, Kami are not separate from nature but are of nature. They are manifestations of Musubi (結び), the interconnecting energy of the universe. Kami are believed to be hidden from this world, and inhabit a complementary existence that mirrors our own; shinkai (神界, "the world of the kami”). To be in harmony with the awe-inspiring aspects of nature is to be conscious of kannagara no michi (随神の道 or 惟神の道, "the way of the kami").

\nThis image is a companion piece to Spectral Crossing. Both images depict an imagined dream sequence of a glimpse into the hidden world.

background_position="top_left" background_repeat="repeat" global_colors_info="{}"]

Since I was young I’ve always felt that the way our society interprets masculine and feminine qualities is totally backwards. The celebrated qualities of the alpha male; being aggressive and quick to anger, dominant and overbearing, insatiably lustful and sexually compulsive… I see these as motivated by weakness and fragility, by a lack of self-awareness and enslavement to a frail ego.

\n

In my world, a ‘real man’ is a man that can cry without shame, a man that bear the pain of facing his own ego, a man that can truly see his flaws and insecurities, a man that is sensitive to how he makes others feel, a man that come overcome the temptations of violent implosion reactions when triggered, a man that can share true intimacy without objectifying or manipulating others, a man that venerates women. The qualities we see as feminine; sensitivity, empathy, nurturance and sweetness… I see these as being powerful and courageous; to be sensitive, to really feel and care in this hurting world necessities tremendous courage and bravery. Its heartbreaking how many of our sisters, daughters and mothers have been abused and face structural oppression every day, but its encouraging that the collective consciousness is growing increasingly intolerant of sexual abuse and toxic masculinity. The resilience and strength of women the world over is a source of constant inspiration. This is dedicated to the fierce cosmic force of the female spirit. RESPECT.

\n

‘A strong woman in her essence is a gift to the world’

\n

- Native American saying

\n

 सर्वमङ्गलमाङ्गल्ये शिवे सर्वार्थसाधिके । शरण्ये त्र्यम्बके गौरि नारायणि नमोऽस्तु ते ॥

\n

ॐ जयंती मंगल काली भद्रकाली कपालिनी । दुर्गा क्षमा शिवा धात्री स्वाहा स्वधा नमोऽस्तु‍ते ॥
